    <annotation>
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position place="head" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>
                        Quanti a[e]stimanda est historia, in qua difficile est decernere, vtra pars prudentior, validior, aut expressa viuidi&ugrave;s, aut omnin&ograve; vtilior.
                    </marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>How valuable a history is, in which it is difficult to establish which part is more prudent, powerful or expressed livelier, or more useful altogether.
            </translation>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position place="tail" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>
                        Pro nouis hominibus: et nouis Inuentis. Neotechnia[e], et neopraxia[e] Apologia. Perge: perge celeri&ugrave;s. Liuius est in manibus. 
                        In quo vno omnes dicendi, agendiq[ue] Imagines, prop&egrave; animata[e].
                    </marginalia_text>
                    <person name="Livy"/>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>In support of new men and new discoveries. A defence of new art and practice. Carry on; carry on faster. 
                It is Livy you are holding in your hands. And in him alone all images of speech and action are virtually brought to life.
            </translation>
        </marginalia>
        
